...Lasher (1993) by Anne Rice is the second novel in her series Lives of the Mayfair Witches. Plot summary The novel begins shortly after the mysterious disappearance of Dr.  Rowan Mayfair, recently married to contractor Michael Curry.  Michael, feeling betrayed by Rowan, has sunk into a depression helped along by the useless drugs prescribed to him after his close encounter with death. ...Elspeth Champcommunal (1888- 10 November 1976) was a British fashion designer and the first editor of Vogue in Britain.  She was influential as a designer in her own right in Paris, with an eponymous brand, later taking on the role of chief designer of Worth London.
